NAME: orig_chn
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The origination channel used by the party that delivered the loan to the issuer.

NAME: loan_age
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The number of calendar months since the mortgage loan's origination date. For purposes of calculating this data element, origination means the date on which the first full month of interest begins to accrue.

NAME: orig_rt
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The original interest rate on a mortgage loan as identified in the original mortgage note.

NAME: orig_trm
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: For fixed-rate, adjustable-rate and Interest-only mortgages, the number of months in which regularly scheduled borrower payments are due at the time the loan was originated.

NAME: oltv
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The ratio, expressed as a percentage, obtained by dividing the amount of the loan at origination by the value of the property.

NAME: ocltv
VARLABEL: Original Combined Loan to Value Ratio (CLTV)
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The ratio, expressed as a percentage, obtained by dividing the amount of all known outstanding loans at origination by the value of the property.

NAME: num_bo
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The number of individuals obligated to repay the mortgage loan.

NAME: dti
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The ratio obtained by dividing the total monthly debt expense by the total monthly income of the borrower at the time the loan was originated.

NAME: fthb_flg
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: An indicator that denotes if the borrower or co-borrower qualifies as a first-time homebuyer.

NAME: purpose
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: An indicator that denotes whether the mortgage loan is either a refinance mortgage or a purchase money mortgage. Purpose may be the purchase of a new property or refinance of an existing lien (with cash out or with no cash out).

NAME: prop_typ
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: An indicator that denotes whether the property type secured by the mortgage loan is a condominium, co-operative, planned urban development (PUD), manufactured home, or single-family home.

NAME: num_unit
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The number of units comprising the related mortgaged property (one, two, three, or four).

NAME: occ_stat
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The classification describing the property occupancy status at the time the loan was originated.

NAME: state
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: A two-letter abbreviation indicating the state or territory within which the property securing the mortgage loan is located.

NAME: mi_pct
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The original percentage of mortgage insurance coverage obtained for an insured conventional mortgage loan and used following the occurrence of an event of default to calculate the insurance benefit, as defined by the underlying master primary insurance policy.

NAME: aqsn_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Loan acquisition date from other banks

LABEL: Loan acquired on or after December 1, 2009.

NAME: orig_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The date of each individual note.

NAME: frst_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The date of the first scheduled mortgage loan payment to be made by the borrower under the terms of the mortgage loan documents.

NAME: last_rt
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: For an adjustable-rate mortgage loan, the maximum percentage points that the interest rate can adjust upward over the life of the loan relative to the initial interest rate.

NAME: msa
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The numeric Metropolitan Statistical Area Code for the property securing the mortgage loan. MSAs are established by the US Office of Management and Budget. An area usually qualifies as an MSA if it is defined by the Bureau of the Census as an urbanized area and has a population of 50,000 or more in a total metropolitan area of at least 100,000. An MSA may consist of one or more counties.

LABEL: Property is not in a designated MSA
Last loan activity date is within 2017

Last loan activity date is within 2020
Last loan activity date is within 2021

NAME: lpi_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The due date of the last paid installment that was collected for the mortgage loan.

LABEL: Last paid installment date is before 2017
Last paid installment date is within 2017
Last paid installment date is within 2018
Last paid installment date is within 2019
Last paid installment date is within 2020
Last paid installment date is within 2021

NAME: fcc_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The date on which the completion of the legal action of foreclosure occurred.

NAME: disp_dte
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The date on which ABC Bank's interest in a property ends through either the transfer of the property to a third party or the satisfaction of the mortgage obligation.

LABEL: Loan not yet entered default/not delinquent for at least 30 days
Loan not yet entered default/not delinquent for at least 60 days
Loan not yet entered default/not delinquent for at least 90 days
Loan not yet entered default/not delinquent for at least 120 days
Loan not yet entered default/not delinquent for at least 180 days

NAME: mod_flag
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: An indicator that denotes if the mortgage loan has been modified.

NAME: pfg_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: A reduction of the UPB owed on a mortgage by a borrower that is formally agreed to by the lender and the borrower, usually in conjunction with a loan modification.

NAME: net_loss
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Net loss for the banks due to loan recovery cost

NAME: net_sev
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Total cash received from the sale of the property net of any applicable selling expenses, such as fees and commissions, allowable for inclusion under the terms of the property sale, as currently reported on the HUD-1 or other settlement statement.

NAME: modtot_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The cumulative loss amount calculated for a mortgage loan resulting from a modification event.

NAME: no_depend
VARLABEL: No of dependent for the main borrower

NAME: new_orig_amt
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The dollar amount of the loan as stated on the note at the time the loan was originated.

NAME: new_last_upb
VARLABEL: UPB at the Time of Removal
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The unpaid principal balance of the loan at the time of removal.

NAME: new_pp_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: The expenses associated with securing and preserving the property including two major categories:  maintenance and repairs. Maintenance costs are associated with preserving the property through normal upkeep, while repairs are associated with either avoiding deterioration of the asset or a marketing decision to help maximize sales proceeds upon final disposition.

NAME: new_ar_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Expenses associated with removing occupants and personal property from an occupied property post foreclosure. Such expenses include relocation assistance, deed-in-lieu fee, and fees and costs associated with eviction actions.

NAME: new_ie_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Expenses and credits associated with preserving the property, including Homeowners Association and other dues; flood, hazard, and MI premiums and refunds; rental income; and title insurance costs.

NAME: new_tax_cost
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Payment of taxes associated with holding the property.

NAME: new_ns_procs
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Total cash received from the sale of the property net of any applicable selling expenses, such as fees and commissions, allowable for inclusion under the terms of the property sale, as currently reported on the HUD-1 or other settlement statement.

NAME: new_ce_procs
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Proceeds from claims on primary and certain other limited mortgage insurance policies, and recourse and indemnification payments from lenders under arrangements designed to limit credit exposure to ABC Bank.

NAME: new_rmw_procs
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Amounts received by ABC Bank under the terms of our representation and warranty arrangements for the repurchase of the mortgage loan or the subject property or loss reimbursement subsequent to property disposition.

NAME: new_o_procs
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Amounts, other than sale proceeds, received by ABC Bank following foreclosure of a property, including redemption proceeds received from the mortgagor.

NAME: new_fmod_upb
VARLABEL: Loan first modification unpaid principal balance

NAME: new_zip_3
ITEM SPECIFIC INFORMATION: Limited to the first three digits of the code designated by the U.S. Postal Service where the subject property is located.
